hwTwampMib.name: hwTwampMib

revisions.description: Add hwTwampSenderSessionNumExceed and hwTwampSenderSessionNumRecovery node for this mib.
Add hwTwampSenderMultiFlowEn node for this mib.
Modify the description of hwTwampSenderTwoWayLossValue node for this mib.
Modify the value range of hwTwampResponderSourceUDPPort, hwTwampResponderDestUDPPort, hwTwampSenderLocalUDPPort and hwTwampSenderRemoteUDPPort nodes for this mib.
Modify the description of hwTwampResponderDestUDPPort and hwTwampSenderRemoteUDPPort nodes for this mib.
Modify the datatype of hwTwampSenderPaddingType nodes for this mib.
Add hwTwampSenderPaddingType hwTwampSenderTwoWayErrorCount hwTwampSenderTwoWayTotalErrorCount nodes for this mib.
Add hwTwampSenderTwoWayTotalSentCount hwTwampSenderTwoWayTotalLossValue nodes for this mib. Add interval00us for this mib.

Add hwTwampTwoWayLossAlarmTable hwTwampTwoWayDelayAlarmTable hwTwampTwoWayJitterAlarmTable nodes for this mib. Add hwTwampTraps and hwTwampResponderIfIndex node for this mib. Add four type alarm node for this mib.
Add units for the hwTwampSenderPadding at 2015-01-09.
Modify description of hwTwampSenderAdminContinual at 2014-10-16. Modify description of hwTwampSenderAdminDuration and hwTwampSenderAdminPacketCount at 2014-10-16.
Add three nodes for this mib.

hwTwampSenderAdminContinual.name: hwTwampSenderAdminContinual
hwTwampSenderAdminContinual.description: This object indicates a proactive or on-demand TWAMP-light test instance. If proactive measurement mode is configured, hwTwampSenderAdminDuration and hwTwampSenderAdminPacketCount cannot be configured. If on-demand measurement mode is configured, hwTwampSenderAdminDuration or hwTwampSenderAdminPacketCount must be configured.

hwTwampSenderAdminDuration.name: hwTwampSenderAdminDuration
hwTwampSenderAdminDuration.description: This object indicates to start the on-demand TWAMP-light test instance with a duration specified. (0 indicates that the object is not configured. If on-demand measurement mode is configured, hwTwampSenderAdminDuration or hwTwampSenderAdminPacketCount must be set. If hwTwampSenderAdminDuration and hwTwampSenderAdminPacketCount are both set, their values cannot all be 0.)

hwTwampSenderAdminPacketCount.name: hwTwampSenderAdminPacketCount
hwTwampSenderAdminPacketCount.description: This object indicates to start the on-demand TWAMP-light test instance with the number of sent packets specified. (0 indicates that the object is not configured. If on-demand measurement mode is configured, hwTwampSenderAdminDuration or hwTwampSenderAdminPacketCount must be set. If hwTwampSenderAdminDuration and hwTwampSenderAdminPacketCount are both set, their values cannot all be 0.)

hwTwampTwoWayLossRatioExceed.name: hwTwampTwoWayLossRatioExceed
hwTwampTwoWayLossRatioExceed.description: A hwTwampTwoWayLossRatioExceed trap is sent when the two-way loss ratio of TWAMP test instance exceeds the uppper threshold in 1-minute statistics period.

hwTwampTwoWayLossRatioRecovery.name: hwTwampTwoWayLossRatioRecovery
hwTwampTwoWayLossRatioRecovery.description: A hwTwampTwoWayLossRatioRecovery trap is sent when the two-way loss ratio of TWAMP test instance is lower than the lower threshold in 1-minute statistics period.

hwTwampTwoWayDelayExceed.name: hwTwampTwoWayDelayExceed
hwTwampTwoWayDelayExceed.description: A hwTwampTwoWayDelayExceed trap is sent when the two-way delay of TWAMP test instance exceeds the uppper threshold in 3 consecutive test periods.

hwTwampTwoWayDelayRecovery.name: hwTwampTwoWayDelayRecovery
hwTwampTwoWayDelayRecovery.description: A hwTwampTwoWayDelayRecovery trap is sent when the two-way delay of TWAMP test instance is lower than the lower threshold in 3 consecutive test periods.

hwTwampTwoWayJitterExceed.name: hwTwampTwoWayJitterExceed
hwTwampTwoWayJitterExceed.description: A hwTwampTwoWayJitterExceed trap is sent when the two-way jitter of TWAMP test instance exceeds the uppper threshold in 3 consecutive test periods.

hwTwampTwoWayJitterRecovery.name: hwTwampTwoWayJitterRecovery
hwTwampTwoWayJitterRecovery.description: A hwTwampTwoWayJitterRecovery trap is sent when the two-way jitter of TWAMP test instance is lower than the lower threshold in 3 consecutive test periods.

hwTwampTwoWayLocExceed.name: hwTwampTwoWayLocExceed
hwTwampTwoWayLocExceed.description: A hwTwampTwoWayLocExceed trap is sent when the two-way loss ratio of the detected network reaches the LOC threshold(100%) in 3 consecutive test periods.

hwTwampTwoWayLocRecovery.name: hwTwampTwoWayLocRecovery
hwTwampTwoWayLocRecovery.description: A hwTwampTwoWayLocRecovery trap is sent when the two-way loss ratio is lower than the LOC threshold(100%) in 3 consecutive test periods.

hwTwampSenderSessionNumExceed.name: hwTwampSenderSessionNumExceed
hwTwampSenderSessionNumExceed.description: A hwTwampSenderSessionNumExceed trap is sent when the number of TWAMP sender session is out of device capability.

hwTwampSenderSessionNumRecovery.name: hwTwampSenderSessionNumRecovery
hwTwampSenderSessionNumRecovery.description: A hwTwampSenderSessionNumRecovery trap is sent when the number of TWAMP sender session is under device capability..
